Encryption at Rest protects stored data, while Encryption in Transit protects moving data.

Encryption at Rest:

* Azure Storage encryption
* Disk encryption

Encryption in Transit:

* HTTPS/TLS
* VPN encryption

For example, stored customer files are encrypted at rest, while uploaded files use HTTPS.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is banking apps securing both storage and communication.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is healthcare systems protecting records end-to-end.

Together, these protections secure data lifecycle.
